caption: Some of the best tacos in the city! This tiny little restaurant knows how to serve big flavor. Portions are big and price is affordable. My fiancé and I eat from here pretty regularly and no matter what we order, the food is delicious.
Best authentic tacos I’ve had in a while. Generous portions, all fresh ingredients. Definitely going back again.

El Rancho Viejo, this mom-and-pop Mexican taqueria is known for its mouth-watering chargrilled steaks capped with mole, full roasted chickens as well as spit-cooked lamb,served up with fresh salsas along with tortillas.

Although large portions, taste was ok.

This place is amazing. Definitely the best Mexican delivery I’ve had in philly. The nachos are delicious. As is basically everything else we ordered. We loved the tortilla soup, the burritos and the chicken tacos.

Delicious and extremely authentic food at an even better price. Hot tortilla chips and meats right off the grill. I got a variety of tacos and my friend got the steak special, which tasted like it was from a steakhouse. Will definitely return.
Sylvestre Rincon is a culinary wizard. Phenomenal tacos and the Massaman nachos are to die for. The horchata is fresh and on point. Best Mex in the neighborhood.

Some of the best Mexican food I’ve ever had. Everything is so fresh and the people are so nice. The salsas they give you at the beginning are incredible and there are lots of vegetarian options. Our new favorite spot for sure!
Amazing food. Amazing price. Chips n sala included Large portion size and the foods just awsome. Workers were very friendly and service is fast

Talk about off the beaten path. Even for those who live in the neighborhood. With just a counter and a few tables this family is as good as it is humble. The folks behind the counter are lovely people, the food comes out hot and flavorful. …
Amazing food - very fresh and made to order - mole was delicious. Chill atmosphere, friendly staff and good service.
Great place amazing food
This place is DELICIOUS! Everything is so fresh, and tasty. I'm not a huge fan of pork, but the 'pastor' is literally to die for, seriously consider it w/ one of the dishes. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!

Fantastic. Massive portions, made to order. Excellent chips and salsas. Really kind people working there. Will def be back.

Went with a large group and shared a bunch of things from the menu. Every single bite of every dish was amazing. Loved the vibe and the service. Great prices. Definitely recommend.
Everything was excellent

Really delicious Mexican food, and it’s run by just the nicest people. Really wonderful.

Really great and slightly different Mexican food. Lighter and more authentic than what you typically find in Philadelphia. Not a ton of dine-in space, so call ahead if you want to eat at the restaurant and not just get take out.

Some of the better Mexican and tacos I have had in Philly. The sauce that goes with everything is some the best spicy sauce I have had. Goes great with everything they have. Authentic and true, can't go wrong with any thing here.
What a great find -- delicious food, wonderful service, great prices and BYO!  We had a great time and definitely will return.  FYI -- it is cash only but there is an ATM on premises.
Very friendly and helpful staff! Went out of their way to accommodate a special order. Food was pretty good too. I had enchiladas with mole sauce and they also have the really thick tortilla chips!
One of if not the best Mexican in philly! Must have!

Great family run business with great service and delicious food. Our server kept stuffing us with more chips and salsa that I nearly lost my appetite for my fish tacos. Portions here are generous are larger than most.
Fresh, delicate flavors. Meats were delicious- both lamb and steak. Owner/chef was so friendly. Lightest, yummiest churos for dessert I ever had. Will return soon.

Easily one of the best meals I've had in the city. We got tacos and the lamb ribs, which were cooked to perfection exactly the way we ordered (medium rare). The staff was helpful and friendly. I'm definitely looking forward to going back. The place is also cash only and BYO.
Super good. Great great service. The people are awesome.

Best Mexican I have had in Philly! The food here is authentic, great value and quality and so delicious!!!! I had the al pastor Cemitas and it was INCREDIBLE. Run by lovely people and can’t wait to try the whole menu
Great authentic Mexican food. I’ve gone twice for the Quesadilla gringa and order of tacos al pastor. I always leave home full or taking leftovers. The staff is very friendly.
Best Mexican food ever!..Everything was as authentic as I have ever enjoyed. Highly recommend....you will NOT be disappointed!
Amazing food!  I just came back from Puebla and the food here is exactly as it is there.  Absolutely loved it!
Stopped in today and enjoyed delicious salmon fish tacos. The owners are lovely people. They make their own delicious tortilla chips and the accompanying sauces are great. Highly recommend.

We moved to S 5th street in early March, and it just so happened that this place opened up just two weeks later. We were really excited to check it out, and finally got the chance to order out on a Friday night. Our expectations were …

So glad El Rancho Viejo has opened up in the neighborhood. It's incredibly fresh and the service is friendly and speedy. You will definitely get a full belly after eating the burritos. Lots of great choices in authentic Mexican cuisine. Thank you Sylvester and Kate and family. Will be visiting again soon.

We've eaten here twice in the last week and everything's been amazing. The pork tacos are my favorite so far and the fried plantains were the best I've had.  Their service is quick and friendly and although we have only gotten take out they do have seating available.
I've gone here the last two days in a row and about to make it three! The pastor tacos are amazing as are the red/green sauces. Glad to have a place so close to home!
Outstanding fresh and modern Mexican cuisine. The beef massaman nachos are out of this world! They are a must try. It's a brand new spot, table space is limited but take-out is speedy.
Happened to walk by at 10pm, peaked in and was offered a free taco...it was their grand opening.  It was really a good, fresh taco.  Will be back to try the rest of their menu!!!
